main event: An unidentified aerial object was observed at Wilmington, Delaware at New Castle City Air Base on 29th October 1957. The objects were described as circular with pale white light and disappeared one by one in a line.
interesting points: The observation lasted only 3 seconds, and the five circular objects disappeared in a small space, each leaving a pale trail.
The objects erased 300 degrees of sky in less than 2 seconds before fading out, following a straight line of flight without any maneuvers.
The observer, 1st Lt. Fox, is described as intelligent and perceptive by CAPT F. Prank, LT COL, USAF, GROUP OPERATIONS STAFF OFFICER.
The report concluded that the objects were probably astronomical (meteor), with insufficient data for evaluation of other possibilities.
There was no air traffic in the area at the time of the sighting, and the observer used ground visual for the observation.
sighted object: Five circular objects with pale white light
location: Wilmington, Delaware at New Castle City Air Base
